XXIX

To Rusrrcus

As it is far better to excel in any single art, than to arrive only at a mediocrity in several; so on the other hand, a moderate skill in several is to be preferred, where one cannot attain to excellency in any. Upon this maxim it is, that 1 have attempted compositions of various sorts, as I could not expect to cany any particular one to its highest point of excellency. 1 hope, therefore, when you read any
